    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2017-06-06</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2017-10-19T18:14:29Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>This bill amends the Federal Power Act to revise the criteria for a facility to qualify as a qualifying conduit hydropower facility.</p> <p>Under current law, a hydropower facility must have a capacity that does not exceed five megawatts.This bill eliminates such requirement.</p> <p>Additionally, the bill revises the timeframe for an entity to contest whether its hydroelectric facility meets the qualifying criteria.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>17</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2017-07-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to House with amendment(s)</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2017-10-17T14:06:20Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>(Sec.1)This bill amends the Federal Power Act to revise the criteria for a facility to qualify as a qualifying conduit hydropower facility.</p> <p>Under current law, a hydropower facility must have a capacity that does not exceed five megawatts.This bill eliminates such requirement.</p> <p>Additionally, the bill revises the time frame from 45 days to 30 days for an entity to contest whether its hydroelectric facility meets the qualifying criteria.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
