        <updateDate>2017-10-17T16:06:29Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>(This measure has not been amended since it was reported to the House on July 12, 2017. The summary of that version is repeated here.)</p> <p>(Sec.1)This bill amends the Federal Power Act to revise the criteria for a facility to qualify as a qualifying conduit hydropower facility.</p> <p>Under current law, a hydropower facility must have a capacity that does not exceed five megawatts.This bill eliminates such requirement.</p> <p>Additionally, the bill revises the time frame from 45 days to 30 days for an entity to contest whether its hydroelectric facility meets the qualifying criteria.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
